#DoseUp @sharisaindia timeless matte liquid lipsticks ✨

These lipsticks have almost a whipped texture and are easy to apply. They’re opaque and MATTE. Once they’re on, they’re on. They don’t even come off when I eat oily food which is crazy 🤯 however, I recommend applying only one layer so it stays on like that otherwise it tends to wear off when eating. It can also be a bit drying so use a good lip balm before application. 
Shade Sinfully Sober is a deepish red colour & Blissfully Lost is a cool toned pink nude shade that I love pairing with a deeper shade outlined. 📦

Let me know what your favourite liquid lipstick is of all time in the comments 👇🏽

I know it sucks to hear but if you have hyperpigmentation on melanated skin it takes some extra effort to get that flawless even tone base 👀

Also important to note that this is just my routine and the techniques that work for me. I’m not a MUA. This typically looks better on camera than it does irl, but that’s true for any makeup look! 🙌🏽

Product Details + products I frequently used that is not shown in the video: 
Primers: @benefitmiddleeast porefessional, @smashboxcosmeticsme primer essence spray, @lakmeindia blur perfect primer 
Corrector: @lagirlcosmetics orange corrector, @n.y.bae corrector, @reachedmars concealer palette 
Concealer: @maccosmeticsindia studio fix concealer NW45 (used here), also I can use @maccosmeticsmiddleeast studio fix concealer NC50, @plumgoodness concealer 135P (code HRITHIKA15)
Powder: @kaybykatrina loose powder pecan, @wearified translucent loose powder (link in bio to shop) 
Sprays: @maccosmeticsindia fix +, @wetnwildindia coconut spray, @officialswissbeauty setting spray 

I hope this helps! Talk to me in the comments! 🫶🏽

 @cosmoindia “Curls might be ‘trending’ today, but when I was growing up, they were equated with untidiness,” says Hrithika Sathish (@thehdose ), Content Creator. “Personally, I was never really conscious of my curly hair until people started telling me things like ‘You look African’, or ‘You’d look so much better with straight hair’. And even though I love my curls, such comments made me wish I had straight hair sometimes. When I catch people staring me, I immediately assume that it is because of my big hair. And I might have hated it in the past, but I like the attention now.” [Smiles]
